<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-08-01T12:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-08-01T12:49:00-05:00" n="339" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/611.</note>
                        <head>[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-08-01T13:00:00-04:49"><hi rend="smallcaps">August</hi> 1, 1911—1 <hi rend="smallcaps">p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>President Simon has informed the diplomatic corps that he is ready to
                            resign and requests three days’ armistice to arrange his affairs and
                            embark on merchant vessel. The diplomatic corps is treating with
                            revolutionists.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>